com.simple_rest.s_rest.restapi.request

Class RequestHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.simple_rest.s_rest.restapi.request.RequestHandler

  • public class RequestHandler
extends java.lang.Object
    this class provides functionalities to work with restful web services. this class provide methods to make a HTTP request using POJO objects by automatically parsing it in JSON format.
    It also parse & return HTTP response to a POJO objects.
    It uses a 'spring framework' for parsing & handling Http request & response.
    Note:- It is mandatory to use other threads then main Activity thread to call methods of this class as they contains network access permission which is not permitted from main Activity thread.
    It is recommended use 'SimpleRequest' or 'ExtendedRequest' instead as they provides higher functionalities & can be used from main activity thread.
    Created by Neel Patel on 24-07-2017.
    Version:
    2.0.0
    Author:
    Neel Patel
    See Also:
    SimpleRequest, ExtendedRequest

      • getResource

        @Nullable
public <T,R> T getResource(@NonNull
                                      java.lang.Class<T> type,
                                      @NonNull
                                      java.lang.String url,
                                      @NonNull
                                      org.springframework.http.HttpMethod meth,
                                      @NonNull
                                      R requestObj,
                                      @NonNull
                                      java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> header)
        this method will make http request using parameters provided. request object will be parsed to json format & Http response will be parsed to a POJO. response body must be JSON representation of generic type 'R'. if generic type 'R' is String then content of the response body will be returned as it is.
        Type Parameters:
        T - class type of expected response body.
        R - class type of HTTP request body.
        Parameters:
        type - class object of expected Http response body.
        url - url.
        meth - Http request method.
        requestObj - body of the Http request.
        header - key value pairs of header parameters.
        Returns:
        return Http response body as object of type 'R'. null otherwise.
